.TH "ni_tio_get_soft_copy" 9 "ni_tio_get_soft_copy" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ni_tio_get_soft_copy \- Safely read the software copy of a counter register.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned int" ni_tio_get_soft_copy
.BI "(const struct ni_gpct *counter "  ","
.BI "enum ni_gpct_register reg "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "counter" 12
struct ni_gpct counter.
.IP "reg" 12
the register to read.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Used to get the software copy of a register whose bits might be modified
in interrupt context, or whose software copy might need to be read in
interrupt context.
